modules.description: Provides logging operations for different severity levels, including message formatting and error handling. Works with log levels, formatted messages, and result types to capture and process errors. Enables structured error recovery with custom pretty-printing and tag management.

This module provides operations for manipulating key-value stores, including insertion, deletion, updates, and queries, alongside functional transformations like mapping, folding, and filtering. It works with a polymorphic type 'a t that maps DNS record keys to values, enabling sequence-based conversions and structured data processing. Use cases include managing DNS record sets or handling structured data pipelines requiring efficient key-based access and transformation.

Processes DNS queries and constructs responses using immutable data structures. Handles DNS message parsing, validation, and generation, working with records like A, AAAA, CNAME, and SOA. Used to implement authoritative DNS servers that manage custom zones and perform reverse lookups for private IP ranges.

Encodes and decodes strings using Base32 encoding, utilizing a custom alphabet defined by an array of integer mappings. It operates on strings and returns results with error handling for invalid input. The module supports padding during encoding and optional unpadded decoding for flexible data processing.

Manages DNS record sets and structured data through key-value operations, supporting insertion, deletion, and transformation via polymorphic types. Implements logging with severity levels, formatted messages, and structured error handling for reliable diagnostics. Enables efficient data processing and error recovery in DNS-related workflows. Examples include updating DNS records and tracking operational events with custom log formats.
